* GitHub Topic:
# How to create GitHub account:
GitHub sign up
Open VM and run the machine > yum -y install git > cd .ssh/ > cat id_rsa.pub > copy ID
Profile settings > SSH and GPG keys > add SSH > name and paste key
Create repo on github > public > Checkamrk "Add README file"
Go to code (in green color) > SSH > Copy id
On VM server- run--- git clone id (SSH ID)
git config --global user.name "username"
git config --global user.email "email id"
(package ill be install in homw directory)


# How to create branches in GitHub
* git branch shows main and new created branch
* git branch -a shows all branches that you created
* To create new branch: git branch branchname
* Now push it into GitHub so: push -u origin branchname
* To switch to another branch: git switch branch name
* To create and switch at the same time: git checkout -b devbranch

